- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security): The paper focuses on the security aspect of IoT networks and proposes a method to ensure secure behavior modeling using blockchain. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper deals with IoT networks and their communication protocols, which falls under the scope of this sub-category. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper uses deep machine learning strategy to analyze the behavior of IoT devices, which falls under the scope of this sub-category. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The paper proposes the use of blockchain technology to ensure secure behavior modeling in IoT networks, which falls under the scope of this sub-category. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper proposes the implementation of a custom Behavior Monitor and Trusted Execution Technology (TEE) to ensure secure behavior modeling in IoT networks, which falls under the scope of this sub-category.
